        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 5:50PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridge Grove, or 8 miles northeast of Camp Hill, moving south at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Opelika, Camp Hill, Lafayette, La Fayette, Waverly, Cusseta, Chambers
County Lake, Beans Mill, Sturkie, Oak Bowery, Ridge Grove, West
Chambers, Roxana, and Mount Jefferson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
